iminal and sinful, including acts officially deemed to be "against nature"-sodomy, bestiality, and masturbation-along with others that approximated the unnatural-hermaphroditism, incest, sex with the devil, solicitation in the confessional, erotic religious visions, and the desecration of holy images. In doing so, this anthology makes important and necessary contributions to the historiography of gender and sexuality. Amid the growing politicized interest in broader LGBTQ movements in Latin America, the essays also show how these legal codes endured to make their way into post-independence Latin America.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aLatin AmericansxSexual behaviorxHistory. 0aSex and lawzLatin AmericaxHistory. 0aSex crimeszLatin AmericaxHistory. 0aSexzLatin AmericaxHistory. 0aSexzLatin AmericaxReligious aspectsxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh1 aTortorici, Zeb, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016z978311066754708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520963184423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520963184.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066754-7  UC Press eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles